2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the integration of the proposed technique with edge learning, which involves training a classifier model using data distributed at edge devices. This makes cs.LG a likely sub-category.
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper mentions the use of a Grassmannian-classification algorithm from computer vision to directly apply the received GAE encoded data to training the model without decoding and conversion. This makes cs.CV a likely sub-category.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the need for high-mobility wireless data acquisition in scenarios where edge devices (or even servers) are mounted on the ground or aerial vehicles.
